OL,7,FHighlighting the implications of the
OL,8,FDay ruling, leading planning lawyer
OL,9,Fand Tory peer Lord Banner said: "A
OL,10,Fhistoric failure to comply with the
OL,11,Fadvertising requirements means that
OL,12,Fthe statutory trust continues to
OL,13,Fexist, and therefore continues to
OL,14,Ffrustrate the beneficial repurposing
OL,15,For redevelopment of the land in
OL,16,Fquestion."
OL,18,FLord Banner added: "This is holding up
OL,19,Fmany developments across the country
OL,20,Fthat already have planning permission.
